author: pburba
msg: Remove some misleading test comments and expectations.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/merge_authz_tests.py
(merge_fails_if_subtree_is_deleted_on_src): Whatever the future may bring
we don't *currently* expect a delete brought down on a local mod by a
merge to result in a tree conflict when using --force.  This test had
comments that indicated we expected a tree conflict.  It even passed
some cryptic expected output to run_and_verify_svn that made it look like
a tree conflict was expected.  But this expected output was created with
expected_merge_output, which creates a regex which happily matches while
ignoring the "expected" tree conflict output.
